ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Shree Ramkrishna Charitable Trust is registered trust. It registered in 1988 and registration number is E/2673/SURAT. Trustees are owner of Diamond Units. Basically it has been registered to help the poor people and especially to the diamond workers. Trust is working on education, health and social field. Trust is more interested to work on education, Health and Social field and HIV/AIDS field. Trust had organized advocacy meeting with industrialist and private practicenar of Surat city in previous years. Trust had also organized Bhagvat BHAGIRITHI SAPTAH to raise local fund for the benefit of PLWHA. We have been working with diamond workers under Partnership for Sexual Health Project since Nov-01 in Katargam and Ved Road area. There are 130000 diamond workers are working in Katargam and Ved road area. Diamond workers are migrated from all over the country but most of them (80%) is migrated from Saurashtra. Most of the diamond workers (68.8%) are young and the age group is 15 years to 30 years. Age group of female diamond workers is 14 years to 30 years but majority are belongs to 14 to 22 years. 60000 (46.2%) of the diamond workers are living with peer. Living with peer diamond workers are living either in KHOLI or in diamond units. Approximate 2000 are commuters. 70000 diamond workers are living with family. Due to the more profit in diamond cutting business more and more people attract towards this work. Diamond workers living far from their family so family has no control over the diamond workers and friends influence is very high and they belong to the young age group. In diamond cutting work they are working for 10 to 12 hours per day and concentration is must needed so by end of the day they look out entertainment and loving support from some one else. Due to this reason they are indulge in HRB activity. Other factors are addiction of liquor, more income, few diamond workers are unmarried and they pass the marriage age so they indulge in high risk activity to satisfy their sexual needs. Similarly, there are watchmen, boys working in video parlor and workers working in the ambrodary work who are living alone and are indulge in HRB activity. Till January 2008 we have implemented targeted intervention project under NACP-II guideline. As per the guideline of NACP â€“ III migrant projects were stopped by GSACS from April 2008. Looking at the need of intervention with migrants we would like to request for the intervention with single male migrant under NAPC - III.
